heroes.name: npc_dota_hero_tidehunter
heroes.bio_loc: The Tidehunter known as Leviathan was once the champion of the Sunken Isles, but his motives are as mysterious as those of his people. We all know the importance of the Drylanders' shipping lanes, how empires may rise and fall according to who controls the open water. Far less is known of the submarine lanes, and how the warring tribes of the Meranthic Diaspora have carved out habitations through endless undersea skirmishes. In the fragile treaties between the Mer and Men, we can glimpse the extent of the drowned empires, but their politics appear complex and opaque. It would seem that Leviathan tired of such petty strife, and set off on his own, loyal only to his abyssal god, Maelrawn the Tentacular. He stalks the shallows now in search of men or meranths who stray into his path, and with a particular loathing for Admiral Kunkka, who has long been his nemesis for reasons lost in the deepest trenches of the sea.
heroes.hype_loc: Stalking ahead of his team, Tidehunter is always on the lookout for the right time to strike. When the moment comes, he unleashes his massive and devastating ultimate, paving the way for his allies to slay their stunned enemies.
heroes.npe_desc_loc: Durable hero who shrugs off enemy damage

abilities.name: tidehunter_gush
abilities.desc_loc: Summons a gush of water to damage an enemy unit, reducing their movement speed and armor.
abilities.lore_loc: During his championship of the Sunken Isles, Leviathan gained mastery over the open sea.
abilities.scepter_loc: Gush becomes a ground targeted wave ability that affects enemy units in a line.  Decreases cooldown.

abilities.name: tidehunter_kraken_shell
abilities.desc_loc:
Thickens Tidehunter's hide to passively block a portion of any incoming physical attack damage. The hide also removes negative status effects if the damage taken crosses a threshold.

Does not stack with items that provide Damage Block.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
abilities.lore_loc: Claddish navymen tell tales of a mighty sea-faring beast that suffered spear and sword but continued to lay waste to the fleet.
notes_loc: Only damage from player owned sources is counted towards debuff removal.
The counter will reset if no player owned damage is taken for %damage_reset_interval% seconds.
Kraken Shell removes most debuffs, even if they are generally not purgable.

abilities.name: tidehunter_anchor_smash
abilities.desc_loc: Tidehunter swings his mighty anchor to attack and deal bonus damage to nearby enemies and reduce their attack damage.
abilities.lore_loc: Stolen from one of Admiral Kunkka's flagships, Leviathan's heavy anchor proves useful as a melee weapon.
notes_loc: Anchor Smash works on all Ancient creeps except for Roshan.
abilities.shard_loc: Anchor Smash now affects buildings and has increased damage and reduced cooldown.

abilities.name: tidehunter_dead_in_the_water
abilities.desc_loc: Tidehunter attaches a heavy anchor to an enemy hero. The hero is leashed while attached to the anchor. Attempting to move more than %chain_length% units away from the anchor forces the hero to %max_movement_speed% move speed, dragging the anchor behind them. The anchor can be destroyed with %attacks_to_destroy% hero attacks.

abilities.name: tidehunter_ravage
abilities.desc_loc: Slams the ground, causing tentacles to erupt in all directions, damaging and stunning all nearby enemy units.
abilities.lore_loc: Calling to the abyssal god Maelrawn has resulted in entire armadas being lost at sea.
notes_loc: Ravage waves move outwards at a speed of %speed%.

talents.name: special_bonus_unique_tidehunter_4
talents.name_loc: +{s:bonus_bonus_reduction_per_stack} Kraken Shell Damage Block per Anchor Smash Kill
talents.desc_loc: Retroactively counts any hero who died with Anchor Smash debuff.

talents.name: special_bonus_unique_tidehunter_8
talents.name_loc: 50% chance of Anchor Smash on attack
